# Data Cleaning & Preparation Project

## Overview

This project was completed as part of the DecodeLabs Data Analytics Internship Program.

The objective of the project was to clean and prepare a raw dataset by identifying missing values, checking duplicates, correcting data formats, and ensuring data quality before analysis.

---

## Dataset Information

- Total Records: 1200
- Dataset Type: Sales / Orders Data
- Tool Used: Microsoft Excel

---

## Data Cleaning Tasks Performed

### 1. Missing Values Handling

- Identified missing values in the CouponCode column.
- Replaced blank values with "No Coupon".

### 2. Duplicate Check

- Checked for duplicate records.
- Verified that no duplicate Order IDs existed.

### 3. Date Formatting

- Standardized all date values into a consistent format.
- Verified that there were no invalid date entries.

### 4. Data Type Validation

Validated the following columns:

| Column | Data Type |
|----------|----------|
| OrderID | Text |
| Date | Date |
| Quantity | Number |
| UnitPrice | Number |
| TotalPrice | Number |

### 5. Data Quality Verification

- Verified dataset consistency.
- Checked for incorrect values.
- Ensured readiness for future analysis and dashboard creation.

---

## Final Result

The dataset was successfully cleaned and prepared for analysis.

### Quality Checks Completed

✅ Missing Values Handled

✅ Duplicate IDs Checked

✅ Date Formats Standardized

✅ Numeric Columns Validated

✅ Dataset Ready for Analysis

